Package: crimeutils
Title: A Comprehensive Set of Functions to Clean, Analyze, and Present Crime Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Jacob", "Kaplan",
    email = "jkkaplan6@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"),
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-0601-0387"))
Description: A collection of functions that make it easier to understand crime (or other)
    data, and assist others in understanding it. The package helps you read data 
    from various sources, cleans it, fixes column names, and graph or map the
    data. 
Depends:
    R (>= 2.10)
Imports:
    dplyr,
    ggplot2,
    gridExtra,
    ggthemes,
    scales,
    magrittr
